## No Repackaging

You may not repackage, rebrand, or redistribute the software or any
substantial portion of it as a standalone software package, library,
tool, or product — whether under a new name or under the ASUKA name —
without explicit prior written permission from the licensor.

This includes, but is not limited to:
  - Publishing a derivative version to a package index (e.g. PyPI, conda)
    under a different name or as a new package;
  - Bundling the software as a core component of another tool or
    framework distributed to third parties;
  - Presenting a derivative as a new or independent research software
    contribution without clear attribution to ASUKA as the origin.

## Noncommercial Purposes

Any noncommercial purpose is a permitted purpose.

Personal use for research, experiment, and testing for the benefit of
public knowledge, personal study, private entertainment, hobby projects,
amateur pursuits, or religious observance, without any anticipated
commercial application, is use for a permitted purpose.

Use by any charitable organization, educational institution, public
research organization, public safety or health organization,
environmental protection organization, or government institution is use
for a permitted purpose regardless of the source of funding or
obligations resulting from the funding.

## Commercial Use

Commercial use of this software requires explicit prior written permission
from the licensor. Commercial use includes, but is not limited to:
  - Use within a for-profit company's internal workflows or products;
  - Integration into commercial software, platforms, or services;
  - Use to provide paid consulting, computation, or research services.

To inquire about a commercial license, contact the licensor via the
repository at https://github.com/zpengmei/ASUKA.

## Citation Requirement

Any academic publication, preprint, report, or presentation that makes
use of this software must cite the following reference:

  Zihan Pengmei. "cuGUGA: Operator-Direct Graphical Unitary Group Approach
  Accelerated with CUDA." arXiv:2601.17729 (2026).
  https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.17729

See also the CITATION.cff file in the repository for additional citation
formats.

